Here are the clean instructions for deploying VMDash on RHEL after `git clone`:

---

## 1. System Packages

```bash
sudo dnf install -y git wget curl python3 python3-devel python3-pip nginx mysql-server
sudo dnf module enable nodejs:18 -y && sudo dnf install -y nodejs
```

## 2. MySQL

```bash
sudo systemctl start mysqld && sudo systemctl enable mysqld
sudo mysql -e "
  CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS ccds_db CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
  CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS proxmox_db CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_unicode_ci;
  CREATE USER IF NOT EXISTS 'admin'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'vssc@123';
  GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON ccds_db.* TO 'admin'@'localhost';
  GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON proxmox_db.* TO 'admin'@'localhost';
  FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
"
```

Import the database dumps (replace `/path/to/vmdash` with your clone path):

```bash
cd /path/to/vmdash/code
mysql -u admin -p'vssc@123' proxmox_db < dbdump.sql
mysql -u admin -p'vssc@123' < seed_active.sql
mysql -u admin -p'vssc@123' < stage_5_migration.sql
```

## 3. Backend Services

### Web Backend (port 5000)
```bash
cd /path/to/vmdash/code/infra-code/web_backend
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Create `.env`:
```env
DB_USER=admin
DB_PASS=vssc@123
DB_HOST=localhost
CCDS_DB_NAME=ccds_db
```

Run:
```bash
gunicorn --workers 3 --bind 0.0.0.0:5000 app:app
```

### Proxmox Backend (port 5001)
```bash
cd /path/to/vmdash/code/infra-code/proxmox_backend
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
pip install ./paramiko-4.0.0-py3-none-any.whl
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Create `.env`:
```env
DB_USER=admin
DB_PASS=vssc@123
DB_HOST=localhost
PROXMOX_DB_NAME=proxmox_db
```

Run:
```bash
gunicorn --workers 3 --bind 0.0.0.0:5001 --timeout 300 app:app
```

## 4. Frontend (option A — dev server on port 3000)

```bash
cd /path/to/vmdash/code/infra-code/frontend
```

Edit `.env` to use direct API URLs:
```env
REACT_APP_HOST_URL=http://<SERVER_IP>:5000
REACT_APP_PROXMOX_URL=http://<SERVER_IP>:5001
```

```bash
npm install --legacy-peer-deps
npm start
```

Access at `http://<SERVER_IP>:3000` with `admin` / `vssc@123`.

## 4b. Frontend (option B — production via Nginx on port 80)

```bash
cd /path/to/vmdash/code/infra-code/frontend
```

Edit `.env` for Nginx proxy paths:
```env
REACT_APP_HOST_URL=/api/web
REACT_APP_PROXMOX_URL=/api/proxmox
```

Build:
```bash
npm install --legacy-peer-deps
npm run build
```

Configure Nginx (`/etc/nginx/nginx.conf`):
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    root /path/to/vmdash/code/infra-code/frontend/build;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }

    location /api/web/ {
        rewrite ^/api/web/(.*)$ /$1 break;
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5000;
    }

    location /api/proxmox/ {
        rewrite ^/api/proxmox/(.*)$ /$1 break;
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:5001;
    }
}
```

```bash
sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl start nginx
sudo setsebool -P httpd_can_network_connect 1
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http && sudo firewall-cmd --reload
```

Access at `http://<SERVER_IP>` with `admin` / `vssc@123`.

